The '''Highlandtown Arts District''' (a.k.a. "ha!" and ''Highlandtown Arts and Entertainment District'') is the largest such designated area in the state of [[Maryland]], encompassing the southeast Baltimore neighborhoods of [[Highlandtown, Baltimore|Highlandtown]], [[Patterson Park]] and portions of the [[Canton, Baltimore|Canton]] and [[Greektown, Baltimore|Greektown]] neighborhoods. In the Highlandtown Arts District, artists live and work in an area known for cultural diversity. The "ha!" district has extensive retail and industrial spaces, along with affordable housing, with easy access to Interstate 95, Interstate 895, [[Fell's Point, Baltimore|Fell's Point]] and [[Downtown Baltimore]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highlandtownarts.com/|work=Highlandtown Arts District|title=What is the Arts & Entertainment District?|accessdate=March 21, 2013}}</ref>
Events held in "ha!" include the Great Halloween Lantern Parade, a farmer's market, the Artket festival, Salsapolkalooza, and Highlandtown Wine Festival.<ref>[http://www.highlandtown.com Highlandtown Wine Festival]</ref>
